decision_conditions:
No development shall be commenced unless and until:
a) an order authorising the realignment of Queensland Road has been made and confirmed;
b) a highway agreement under Section 38 and/or Section 278 of the Highways Act 1980 authorising the proposed alterations and improvements to Queensland Road has been entered into with all relevant parties and completed;
c) the bond required under the agreement referred to in paragraph b) above is in force in respect of the proposed highway works relating to Queensland Road.

REASON: To ensure that the re-aligned Queensland Road will relate to the existing highway network and is of a appropriate standard, in accordance with policy T55 of the Islington UDP (2002).
